The paper discusses a problem related to software engineering research, specifically in the areas of specification discovery, specification mining, and process mining. These areas are typically covered by the sub-category cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also mentions the comparison of behaviours of software systems, which involves aspects of programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper proposes measures to assess the quality of process specifications, which relates to the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed measures to capture precision and recall, which is a common topic in the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
